President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate James Patrick Arguelles, a Superior Court Judge in Sacramento County, California, to serve as a Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of California. Prior to becoming a judge, Arguelles worked as a Partner at Stevens, O'Connell & Jacobs, LLP, an Assistant United States Attorney for the Eastern District of California, and in private practice at Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher, LLP. He is also a Military Judge in the United States Army Reserve. Arguelles earned his B.S. from the United States Naval Academy, his M.S.S. from the United States Army War College, and his J.D. magna cum laude from Harvard Law School.